<font color="#FF0000">COMMUNISTS UNDER THE BED</font><br>
<tt>Wed Aug 20  0:56:00 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
Cook,<br>
     It still amazes me that you insist on labeling nearly everything or everyone you oppose as &quot;Conmmunist&quot;.  Yes, Communists are atheists, but they make up only a small percentage of atheists in the world, especially if one includes the millions that profess to believe in a deity or deities, but are practicing atheists in their everyday lives.  Besides, where does that put DocDel?  And he certainly has principles.                                   <br><br>
It would be nice if Communists had a monopoly on all evil, but there are Nazis, Fascists, corporate greedheads, violent criminals and all sorts loose on the planet.  <br><br>
Would note that it's not abolutely necessary to dehumanize the enemy in warfare to get a great amount of carnage.  During our Civil War, brothers, cousins, friends and old classmates wound up on opposite sides, often in the same battle.  Yet that war still holds the record for deaths and casulaties in both percentage of population, absolute numbers, bloodiest battle and bloodiest single day.  
<p><code>-- gerald_ney@icpphil.navy.mil  (Gerald Ney, &quot;professor&quot;, 7/68-7/69) </code><p>


